(-1)^n \sum_{k=0}^n {n\choose k} (-1)^{n-k} k^m
A(z) = \sum_{n\ge 0} (-1)^n \frac{z^n}{n!} = \exp(-z).
B(z) = \sum_{n\ge 0} n^m \frac{z^n}{n!} =  z \exp(z) \sum_{q=1}^m {m \brace q} z^{q-1},
A(z) B(z) = z \sum_{q=1}^m {m \brace q} z^{q-1}.
(-1)^n n! [z^n] A(z) B(z) =  (-1)^n n! [z^{n-1}] \sum_{q=1}^m {m \brace q} z^{q-1} = (-1)^n n! {m \brace n}.
